ctively, we need to consider its limits. This collection is a welcome new addition to the anthropology of religion, offering fresh debates on a classic topic and drawing attention to meaning in a way that other volumes have for key terms like "culture" and "fieldwork.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aAnthropology of religionvCongresses. 0aChristianity and culturevCongresses. 0aEthnologyxReligious aspectsxChristianityvCongresses. 0aMeaning (Philosophy)xReligious aspectsxChristianityvCongresses. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Pentecostal & Charismatic.2bisacsh1 aBornstein, Erica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColeman, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngelke, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngelke, Matthew, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFaubion, James D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGershon, Ilana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrta, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobbins, Joel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRutherford, Danilyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTomlinson, Matt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTomlinson, Matt, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978085745709740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780857457097423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780857457097/original  a978-3-11-099828-3  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000